      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nausea and tremors are common side effects when you're first starting lithium, but you should definitely be proactive about it. Since you're feeling these things, it's very important to immediately check your sodium levels and perhaps take a dose of Vitamin B6 to help stabilize your system. Don't hesitate to reach out to your prescribing physician to discuss these symptoms, as they can adjust your dosage or suggest supportive care.",
